originalText.text: Yolanda was an incredible help when we decided to move to NYC, and from our first call, I felt we were in the right hands. She was assuring, charismatic, patient with all my questions, and quick to ease any of my anxieties. We spent two days seeing places around Manhattan, and I can't imagine doing that with any other agent. What impressed me the most about Yolanda was the quality of the places she had for us to see. We made a little wish list of all the features I was looking for, and even in the shrinking NYC real estate market, we were able to find a great place with almost everything we were looking for. If you can, get in touch with Yolanda, and she will do everything in her power to provide you with what you need.

originalText.text: Yolanda helped me and my wife move to NYC. When people say moving to the city is complicated, that's an understatement. There's so much to know when moving here which is so different to moving anywhere else in the world. Yolanda helped us secure renting a co-op (again which was a whole new concept in itself). The weekend we chose to apartment hunt was less than ideal, Labor day weekend. Even then, Yolanda was able to set up a bunch of places for us to look at. Throughout the whole process she was calm and kind, even with all our questions. One thing she really excels at is teaching people about all the ins and outs of moving here. Like I said, it's complicated, however Yolanda always takes the time to explain things really well, and never gets frustrated or annoyed when you don't just know these things. She was able to handle all the paperwork with ease and help us secure our dream apartment. It was truly invaluable having her on our team for moving and I would highly recommend anyone taking her on as a broker.

originalText.text: For a first time homebuyer, the process can be pretty nerve-wracking, but Yolanda really went above and beyond at every step of the way to help me find a place I love. First, she really took the time to understand what I was looking for (and, even more valuably, helped me narrow that down for myself and figure out what I really wanted.) Then, at every step of the process from mortgage lenders to viewing places to making an offer to preparing the packet and interview, she made sure I understood the steps and timeline. Any speed bumps that arose during the process (a disappearing lawyer, a pushy seller's agent), were handled calmly and professionally. She's a genuine champion for her clients and dedicated to helping them find the right place - and I really felt throughout the process that she had my back. I've already referred Yolanda to a friend looking to buy and can't recommend her highly enough.
